static void cleanup_resource ( struct ldlm_resource *  res,
struct list_head *  q,
__u64  flags 
) [static]

Cancel and destroy all locks on a resource.

If flags contains FL_LOCAL_ONLY, don't try to tell the server, just clean up. This is currently only used for recovery, and we make certain assumptions as a result--notably, that we shouldn't cancel locks with refs.
